            <h4>Card Sorting</h4>

            <p>I organised a card sorting exercise on <a href="https://www.optimalworkshop.com/">Optimal Workshop</a> to
                find out how users naturally group the content
                and name the sections.</p>
            <p>The results? A couple of sections of the page weren't groups users naturally thought of, and users chose
                section names that are more descriptive and shorter than the existing ones.</p>
            <p>I presented these results to the team. There were surprises, but we managed to
                agree on a new structure to test. Here are some examples of changes:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>A lot of content about
                    activities and food existed as collapsed subsections under a "Your Hotel" section, which we removed.
                </li>
                <li>Some sections got merged, like "More Flights Options" and "Your Flight Details" that became "Flights
                    & Transfers", or "Just for Kids", "Sports and Relaxation" and "Everything else" that became
                    "Activities".
                </li>
                <li>Some sections got different names (e.g. "Swim & Sun" became "Pool & Beach", "What's included in the
                    packages?" became "Packages", etc.)
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Tree Testing</h4>

            <p>We needed to validate our proposition before changing thousands of product pages. The tasks in the test
                were set up using the most frequently asked questions to customer service. There
                wasn't much buy-in in sister companies in Germany, Belgium and the Netherlands: they felt some things
                would only work in English. So
                I got help from colleagues there to set up similar tests in German, French and Dutch.</p>
            <p>The results? In most cases, increased success rate, less hesitation and lower completion times. But there
                were a few things to fine tune. For instance, a section about the location of the hotel was added
                (instead of having that information in the general blurb about the hotel). I organised a new test to
                validate this new proposition.
            </p>
            <h4>Re-design and validate</h4>
            <p>In some cases, design changes were needed in order to fit the new structure. This
                was for instance the case with the videos of hotels. In those cathat the designe rprototyped and I
                tested with users.
            </p>
