    {{#> case/paragraphe title="Results" }}
        <p>With the new structure:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Content is organised in sections that reflect what users are looking for.</li>
            <li>Section names are short and describe exactly what each section contains, in users' own
                words.
            </li>
            <li>The structure is more flat: 2 levels of headings instead of 4.</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Changes were gradually rolled out to measure effects. For instance:
            <ul>
            <li>Changes around Room Details and Board Type led to an increase of 3.5% in conversions.</li>
            <li>The new location and design for videos led to an increase of 349% in users engaging with that content
            (and interacting with the video has the highest associated conversion rate of all
            clickable elements on the page).</li>
            </ul>


